post_text: Through a Federal School Lunch Waiver ALL students at Sheridan Schools may eat breakfast and lunch at no cost from now until the end of December or until federal funds are depleted whichever comes first. Returning SHS students going into 9th grade - if you were unable to attend our first early Chromebook distribution night, we are having one more this week. Returning SHS students going into 9th grade can pick up their Chromebooks early if desired on:

Thursday, 7/30 from 3:30-6:30 pm in front of the SHS Media Center (please social distance if there is a line when you arrive).

Students MUST have the 1:1 Responsible Use Agreement (emailed to all freshman parents) signed by BOTH student and guardian and MUST turn in their 8th grade Chromebook in order to receive their new device.

If you are unable to print the agreement from home, blank ones will be on hand, however the MUST be signed by student and guardian that evening.

If you have any questions, please email leaj@sheridan.k12.in.us

Great news for our Blackhawks - we will be extending our lunch program through June in conjunction with the Methodist Church's Lunch Club.

STARTING MAY 27th - the SCS lunch ladies will be distributing 3 lunches each WEDNESDAY for Wednesday-Friday. This will be done from 1 location at the old IGA.

The Sheridan First United Methodist Church will be serving lunches to the community (students and adults) each Monday and Tuesday (as well as adult lunches all week at the church).

NEXT WEEK-you can pick up lunches as usual (Monday & Wednesday at our 3 locations) through May 22nd. This summer schedule starts MAY 27th.

post_text:
A message from our SHS Guidance Dept.
The Indiana Commission for Higher Education has extended the filing deadline for the 2020-2021 Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) beyond the state’s original April 15 deadline. The extension is intended to ensure as many Hoosiers as possible can access financial aid in the coming academic year in the midst of challenges presented by the coronavirus.
Seniors and parents please check your email for more information!

post_text:
Seniors were emailed this information, but as a reminder:

The FAFSA deadline still remains April 15th. The Indiana Commission of Higher Education will be having FAFSA Frenzy on April 4th online from 1-3 PM. Commission staff will be answering questions through Facebook (facebook.com/LearnMoreIN), Instagram (@LearnMoreIndiana) and Twitter (@LearnMoreIN). For one-on-one help, they will have students call our outreach staff and our partners at INvestEd. They will have staff assisting people in Spanish if needed.
